⟦ Node.js Console FFI Type Declarations

  Provides typed FFI declarations for the Node.js console module.
  Import this module to get compile-time type checking for console methods.

  Example:
    i stdlib::ffiNodeConsole
    λmain()=>Unit=console.log("typed!")
⟧

e console:{
  debug:λ(String)=>Unit,
  error:λ(String)=>Unit,
  info:λ(String)=>Unit,
  log:λ(String)=>Unit,
  warn:λ(String)=>Unit
}
